{"_id":"PrincessTuvstarr","name":"Princess Tuvstarr - The Child Princess","type":"npc","img":"icons/equipment/head/crown-jeweled-gold-pink.webp","system":{"npcType":"broken_one","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":true,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":2,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a pure and innocent soul","I just want a world without suffering"],"agenda":"I want to stay forever in my perfect world. I have been here for so long that I have forgotten what my life was like before","gifts":[{"name":"Creative Will","description":"Tuvstarr has the power to create anything she wants in the Dream World. She can make a bird appear out of nowhere or make an apple tree grow from nothing to bearing fruit in a couple of seconds. She can deflect a river, make sunlight warmer, shape clouds, and make small fish glow around her when swimming in a river. Each new creation draws life from the real world, making it more corrupt and darker. Tuvstarr can use her power to defend herself by literally manipulating the whole world. If Tuvstarr is killed in this world, she will transform into colorful butterflies to regenerate herself at her castle. Although Tuvstarr has virtually infinite power, her innocence means that even if threatened, she will never try to kill a living being. Rather, the Princess will try to hurt and scare any threats and, in the worst case, drive them away."},{"name":"Pure Innocence","description":"Tuvstarr radiates innocence and beauty. Whoever meets her will fall under her spell. She is always friendly, and her voice is clear and beautiful, with the sharpness of ice breaking on a winter pond. Those who interact with Tuvstarr must make a Defense Check or be fascinated by her. For the rest of the Scene, the bewitched subject will not take any action that could harm Tuvstarr and, furthermore, will defend her at the cost of their life from any threats. Seeing how the world outside the pond is rotting will make a bewitched subject instantly come to their senses."}],"background":"A child princess who learned of a pond deep in the woods where wishes can come true. She asked Skutt the moose to lead her there, trading her crown to the Fairies and her dress to the Hulder for safe passage. At the black pond, she plunged her heart and soul in, desiring a perfect world where everything is bright and good. That's what she found on the other side - a perfect dream where she is happy, fields are always green, and idealized constructs of her parents smile at her. But the Dream World needs balance, and so reality became dark and twisted: the sun set in eternal darkness, the forest corrupted, animals got sick, and the soil rotted. She wanders naked and full of life in her dream kingdom, creating things with her power. She has only vague memories of the real world, as if that were the dream. There is something about the black pond that makes her uncomfortable or even scares her, but she cannot 'remove' it as it is the gateway between worlds. She will ask visitors to stay in her kingdom forever, just like the Gallant Knight did."},"flags":{"scenarioId":"tuvstarrs-reflection","role":"main-antagonist-innocent","location":"dream-world-castle","power-source":"wish-magic"}}
{"_id":"TheHulder","name":"The Hulder - Corrupted Forest Spirit","type":"npc","img":"icons/creatures/unholy/spirit-undead-ghost-blue.webp","system":{"npcType":"broken_one","oppositionLevel":7,"isMainNPC":true,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am an ancient forest spirit","I have eaten so many living things that I have become fat and swollen","The pieces of the animals and people I have devoured are dripping from my slobbering lips"],"agenda":"Devour everything I meet","gifts":[{"name":"Corrupted Spirit","description":"The Hulder has a feminine form, thin but her skin is spongy and slimy. Her breath smells of rot. She doesn't realize what a grotesque monster she has become, as in her mind she is still beautiful and seductive. When she suffers 1 Wound, the Hulder vomits a cloud of foul vapor that reeks of rot. All the subjects hit by the cloud suffer 1 Wound in turn. The effect of this Gift can be avoided with a Defense Check."},{"name":"Swollen with Flesh and Blood","description":"If killed, the Hulder will emit a long, heart-breaking cry that will echo in the woods, and all the dead she has eaten will scream in agony in a cacophonous chorus. Anyone who hears the cry loses 2 Soma and receives 1 Penalty on any action for the rest of the Scene."}],"background":"A spiritual forest entity with feminine traits that once lived in symbiosis with trees but is now corrupt and repulsive. When Princess Tuvstarr traded her white dress for passage through the woods, the Hulder took the thin fabric and immediately felt unlike anything before. With the dress, she felt strong and beautiful, but also prey to a voracious hunger. Now the dress is nothing more than a dirty piece of cloth tied over her eyes like a blindfold. The Hulder obsessively repeats how beautiful, graceful and lovely she is, unaware of the grotesque monster she has become. A trail of blood and slime marks her path. Her sense of smell is almost non-existent, but she charges furiously at any noise. The best way to defeat her is to tear the dress from her eyes near a reflective surface - when she sees her true reflection, she will scream in agony and crawl away to throw up everything she ate, returning to her original form filled with shame and guilt."},"flags":{"scenarioId":"tuvstarrs-reflection","role":"corrupted-guardian","location":"dark-forest","weakness":"reflection"}}
